m:MaterialTitle.title: Usage
m:MaterialTitle.description: Here is a backgroundColor palette based on the material design base backgroundColors. Each of these backgroundColors is defined with a base backgroundColor class and an optional lighten or darken class.

m:MaterialLabel.text: To apply a background backgroundColor, just add the backgroundColor name and light/darkness as a class to the element.
This is a Material Panel with a TEAL_LIGHTEN_2 class

g:HTMLPanel.demo:PrettyPre: <m:MaterialPanel backgroundColor="TEAL_LIGHTEN_2"> <m:MaterialLabel text="This is a Material Panel with a TEAL_LIGHTEN_2 class" /> </m:MaterialPanel>

m:MaterialLabel.text: To apply a text backgroundColor, just append -text to the backgroundColor class like this:
This is a Material Panel with dark BLUE text

g:HTMLPanel.demo:PrettyPre: <m:MaterialPanel backgroundColor="BLUE-text text-darken-2" textAlign="CENTER"> <m:MaterialLabel text="This is a Material Panel with dark BLUE text" /> <m:MaterialPanel>

m:MaterialTitle.title: Color Tool
m:MaterialTitle.description: A new resource for creating color schemes, testing accessibility, and previewing your UI in color
